comments: Lots of good talks this semester.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: More cognitive work, or more developmental work that isn't strictly moral/social cognition

I found the series this semester to be extremely focused on moral development, which isn't something of major interest to me. I may just not know enough about this subfield to appreciate the differences amongst different speakers, but ended up feeling that a lot of the talks seemed kind of the same or became sort of inside baseball events where faculty who were interested in this topic had a lot to say and those of us knowing less about the nuances didn't get very engaged.
It was very hard to be a cog student here --- it was mostly about developmental morality, something that is very distal to my personal research --- I would love it if cog lunch came back
